    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-07-04T03:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-07-04T03:00:00-05:00" n="662"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d662">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">851.01/7–444: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Acting American Representative to the French Committee of
                        National Liberation at Algiers</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Chapin</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Algiers</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-07-04T10:00:00+02:00"
                            >July 4, 1944—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 10:16 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2266. Reference my 2254 July 3, 12 noon. Following two names have been added to
                    the party, Lieutenant Colonel Hartemann of the Air General Staff, and André
                    Laguerre, Chief of de Gaulle’s Press Bureau. Major Fitts of ATC,<note n="46"
                        xml:id="d662fn46">Air Transport Command (USAAF).</note> although not a
                    [member of] party, is accompanying it to insure smoothness of trip.</p>
                <p>Members of party including myself but not including Fitts total 12.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Chapin</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
